    <h1 class="full-width center">Chamber Concerts</h1>
    <p class="full-width">
      ICFA hosts chamber concerts periodically. Unique works of art, dance,
      theatre, etc, are presented to the audience at the center. The performance
      area is fitted with lights and efforts are made to create the black box
      effect with the screens and flooring. The space sits approximately 40
      individuals.
    </p>
    <p class="full-width">
      Several objectives are met through this process. The events are ticketed
      and the performing artists are compensated. Events like such bridge the
      gap between the performer and the audience and bring in a different
      dimension to performing arts by creating a platform for communication. The
      audience gets an insight into the process of the artist and the artist
      gets real time feedback from the audience. The Q&A which follows is a two
      way learning process and makes space for growth.
    </p>
    <p class="full-width">
      Several artists of repute have brought in their work.
    </p>
